  "text": "Surface Laptop 2024 (13.8-inch) Touchscreen There are plenty of reasons to grab a Surface Laptop this Prime Day. Perhaps you're on a Windows 10 device, and you want to grab a new one so you can use Windows 11 before the older operating system falls out of support. Maybe you're interested in Copilot+, and you want a device that supports it. Or perhaps you just want a shiny new Arm processor to see what Windows on Arm can do. Related Best upgradeable laptops in 2025 Take a look at these great laptops that you can upgrade yourself after purchase Whatever your motives, you can now grab a Surface Laptop at a 34% discount this Prime Day sale. That's a $481 saving, bringing its regular price down to a cool $918.99. However, you only have until July 11th to grab it, so be sure to act fast. Why the Surface Laptop 2024 is worth your time and money The most notable part of this deal is how recent the hardware is. As you might expect from the name, the Surface Laptop 2024 version came out only last year, so the hardware is still very recent. Plus, it uses a Snapdragon X Elite processor, meaning you can give Windows on Arm a try. This version of Windows takes advantage of the unique Arm architecture, and apps load faster and feel snappier as a result. Microsoft's big drive with its Snapdragon X laptops is turning them into Copilot+ machines. These are special devices that can run Copilot AI tasks locally, so if you're into using Microsoft's assistant to help get things done, Copilot+ is perfect. However, even if you never touch the Copilot features, the Surface Laptop 2024 is still an excellent purchase; the hardware alone makes it worth your money. With $481 taken off of the asking price, now is a great time to make the upgrade to a Surface Laptop. Just be sure to snag it before July 11th, when it'll return to its regular price.",
